{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fireAndForget"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/FireAndForget","preciseIdentifier":"s:12Dependencies13FireAndForgetV","text":"FireAndForget"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Useful as a controllable and testable substitute for a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task { }"},{"type":"text","text":" that performs some work off"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into the void. In tests, the operation becomes structured, and the async context that kicks"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"off the work will wait for it to complete before resuming."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, suppose you are building a server application that has an endpoint for updating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a user’s email address. To accomplish that you will first make a database request to update"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user’s email, and then if that succeeds you will send an email to the new address to let"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user know their email has been updated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, there is no need to tie up the server in order to send the email. That request"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t return any data of interest, and we just want to fire it off and then forget about it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"One way to do this is to use an unstructured "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":" like so:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await self.database.updateUser(id: userID, email: newEmailAddress)","Task {","  try await self.sendEmail(","    email: newEmailAddress,","    subject: \"Your email has been updated\"","  )","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, this kind of code can be problematic for testing. In a test we would like to verify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that an email is sent, but the code inside the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":" is executed at some later time. We"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would need to add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task.sleep"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task.yield"},{"type":"text","text":" to the test to give the task enough time to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"start and finish, which can be flakey and error prone."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"So, instead, you can use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/fireAndForget"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency, which creates an unstructured task"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when run in production, but creates a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"structured"}]},{"type":"text","text":" task in tests:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await self.database.updateUser(id: userID, email: newEmailAddress)","self.fireAndForget {","  self.sendEmail(","    email: newEmailAddress,","    subject: \"You email has been updated\"","  )","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now this is easy to test. We just have to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":" for the code to finish, and once it does"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"we can verify that the email was sent."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/dependencies\/dependencyvalues\/fireandforget"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/fireAndForget","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A dependency for firing off an unstructured task."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"fireAndForget","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fireAndForget"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"FireAndForget","preciseIdentifier":"s:12Dependencies13FireAndForgetV"}],"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:12Dependencies16DependencyValuesV13fireAndForgetAA04FireeF0Vvp","extendedModule":"Dependencies","modules":[{"name":"Dependencies"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Dependency values","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/calendar","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/context","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/continuousClock","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/date","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/locale","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/mainQueue","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/mainRunLoop","doc:\/\/Dependencies\/documentation\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/openURL","doc:\/\/Depende